objectivesList.presetDescription: 1. Selecting the data mining technique(s) that fulfil the defined process objectives and suit the targeted metabolomics data.
objectivesList.customisedDescription: 1. Selecting the data mining technique(s) that fulfil the defined process objectives and suit the targeted metabolomics data.

objectivesList.presetDescription: 2. The selected technique performance must be measurable in model evaluation.
objectivesList.customisedDescription: 2. The selected technique performance must be measurable in model evaluation.

objectivesList.presetDescription: 3. The selected technique must have the potential to achieve the defined process ob- jective.
objectivesList.customisedDescription: 3. The selected technique must have the potential to achieve the defined process ob- jective.

objectivesList.presetDescription: 4. The application of the selected technique must be feasible, and it must consider the process management constraints and available resources.
objectivesList.customisedDescription: 4. The application of the selected technique must be feasible, and it must consider the process management constraints and available resources.

objectivesList.presetDescription: 5. The selection procedures must be comprehensive and unbiased, and it must cover all possible data mining techniques (see section 3.4).
objectivesList.customisedDescription: 5. The selection procedures must be comprehensive and unbiased, and it must cover all possible data mining techniques (see section 3.4).

objectivesList.presetDescription: 6. The selection strategy must be flexible and adjustable and consider the selection of alternative techniques in the case of feedback or iteration.
objectivesList.customisedDescription: 6. The selection strategy must be flexible and adjustable and consider the selection of alternative techniques in the case of feedback or iteration.

objectivesList.presetDescription: 7. The selection of white-box data mining techniques must be encouraged over the selection of the black-box ones, as they allow more justification, reasoning, and explanation of the modelling results.
objectivesList.customisedDescription: 7. The selection of white-box data mining techniques must be encouraged over the selection of the black-box ones, as they allow more justification, reasoning, and explanation of the modelling results.

objectivesList.presetDescription: 8. The selection must consider the possibility of using more than one data mining technique.
objectivesList.customisedDescription: 8. The selection must consider the possibility of using more than one data mining technique.
